### Phase 2: Authentication + User Management

Implementing OAuth2 providers and user authentication:
- OAuth2 provider initialization (Google, Apple, Microsoft, GitHub, Facebook)
- Session management with gorilla/sessions
- JWT token generation and validation
- Auth handler with provider discovery
- Frontend auth store (zustand with persistence)
- Protected routes and auth callback page
- Updated Header with user menu and logout
- Dashboard with overview, properties, analytics, profile pages
- Enhanced API client with auth support

**Phase 2 Complete:**
- Backend OAuth2 integration with goth library
- Frontend authentication flow
- Protected routes
- User session persistence
- Dashboard UI

---

### Phase 3: Property Management Core

Implementing hierarchical property management:
- Property CRUD with full lifecycle (draft, published, archived)
- Dwelling entities (houses, apartments, barns, etc.)
- Room entities with floor assignment
- Area entities (gardens, fields, outdoor spaces)
- Media upload with MinIO/S3 integration
- Content versioning with rollback support
- Geographic data queries with PostGIS (radius search)
- Complete API endpoints for all entity types
- Full handler/service/repository implementations

**Phase 3 Complete:**
- Property CRUD with slug generation and geospatial queries
- Hierarchical structure: Property → Dwellings → Rooms, Property → Areas
- Media service with S3-compatible storage (MinIO)
- Content versioning with version history and rollback
- Authorization middleware with role-based access
- All repositories implemented with GORM
- API routes fully wired up
- Fixed flake.nix for current nixpkgs (package name updates)
- Backend and frontend both build successfully

